Discussion of Six-Month Results
 
Net Income From Continuing Operations grew 99% to $3,701,109 or $0.66 per diluted share for the six months ended June 2007 as compared to $1,856,532 or $0.35 per diluted share in the six months ended June 2006. Revenues grew 54% to $64.7 million in the six months ended June 2007 from $42.0 million in the six months ended June 2006. Revenues in the Companys Caretenders Visiting Nurse (VN) segment grew 90% over the same period last year.
 
The number of weighted average shares outstanding for purposes of calculating diluted earnings per share increased 6% between periods.
 
